- The program prompts the user to enter the target word.
- It opens the file for reading and reads each line.
- For each line, it tokenizes the line into individual words using the `istringstream` object.
- It compares each word with the target word using the `==` operator.
- If the words match, it increments the count using the `++` operator.
- After reading all lines, it closes the file and displays the word occurrence count.
